Something about train travel is so special. Maybe I’m a romantic, but it transports you not only in space, but in time- allowing you to glimpse into a generation not quite forgotten, but perhaps disregarded.

And if I ever have to chose a train to take, it will undoubtedly be the @vsoetrain by @belmond

Paris December 2022 VS Paris December 2016

Can you tell which one is happier? 😝

All I can tell you is that these are two very different women in each of these photos. Sure, the core of each is the same, but the life lived in a span of six years, has altered the world of the woman in these photos.
The 2016 version of me went to Paris with less than €250 in her bank account for an entire weekend, completely solo.  She was recently single, and couldn’t even dream up the later version. She had just started a blog and was hungry for the world around her, but unsure where to begin.
2022 sydney went to Paris with much more money than that in her pocket (thankfully) and was on her way for one of the most authentic travel experiences ever on board the @vsoetrain & to attend the world’s leading luxury travel event in Cannes. She isn’t just hungry for the world, she loves it and those she’s with.

And while they are two totally different people, I would never have been one without the other. Without the dreams and tiny blog that started in 2016, I wouldn’t have had the passion or the drive to reach where I am at the end of 2022. And without the 2016 version of me, I wouldn’t now possess the experience to tell you to NEVER throw away your Paris metro tickets, lest you be robbed of your last remaining euros  by the French police 😅
Always remembering this beautiful life is about ~balance~
Happy holidays ✨#TheBohoDoesFrance

It’s me, hi 👋🏼 I’m the problem it’s me 👋🏼

And the problem is…an addiction to travel!  There’s been a lot of coming and going around here lately so I wanted to do a quick intro into who I am and what you guys can expect here (and if you don’t like it- don’t let the screen door hit ya where the universe split ya😉)

Here goes 🥂

I’m Sydney!

I stepped on board my first plane in 2015 in a once in a lifetime trip to spend the summer in Italy. A year later, I went back, only planning to stay three months (I ended up staying a year)

During that time I started this teeny tiny little travel blog called The Boho Traveller. You see, I’ve always loved bohéme ideals, and my ancestors are from Bohemia, fitting like a brand new pair of leather boots ready to be worn in.

I started the blog because everyone i knew back at home kept asking me how I managed to move to Italy!  The answer was quite simple: not easily 😂

While I lived in Italy I worked in the office for a student travel company in social media and marketing. I also worked part time as a tour guide. 😁

Safe to say, I caught the travel bug hard. I moved back to Florida, where I am from, and continued to travel every chance I got. Morocco, Iceland, Ecuador, Peru, Mexico, Alaska, Canada, the UK…and the list goes on.

The blog and my instagram account grew, and I had this feeling I could do something more!

That’s when I joined the team @explorateurtravel - several people sent me a post that @jennifermjacob was hiring and it seemed like the perfect fit at the perfect time.

When Covid hit I took to yachting as the times were tough, but if you follow my newsletter, you know that after 3 summer season, I’ve retired from a life at sea 🌊

Last year I only brought on new clients for half the year and brought home more money than I was earning in yachting. It was a sign it was time to leave.

I went on over 20 trips, booked over 60 client trips, and won an award. In attended two industry trade shows and went on four FAM trips!

There is so much more to the story, but instagram caps my character count…but you can expect more travel, more adventure, and more luxury coming your way soon! #TheBohoTraveller #RuggedLuxury
It honestly really is fantastic to get to experience travel for work🧡 just remind me of that on days where there are hundreds of flight cancellations 😂 #TheBohoDoesSweden

‼️ NEW ENTRY REQUIREMENTS FOR TRAVELLERS TO EUROPE ‼️ Starting in November 2023, the EU will be instituting the ETIAS System, a program that will require American and Canadian travellers to register with BEFORE they travel to Europe.
ETIAS will also require a small fee of $7 for entry into the EU.
This is very similar to the immigration Visa Fee Authorisation that the United States has in place for travellers from the EU called ESTA.

The program doesn’t start until later this year (originally intended to begin in May!) but make sure you are prepared before you travel!

It’s Friday… so let’s jump on in? Maybe not like this… The Silfra fissure in Iceland may be some of the world’s clearest water for diving- but it is not for the faint of heart. 🧊

Don your dry suit for snorkeling or if you’re a complete lunatic, put on your wetsuit and dive this continental rift for a truly chilly and thrilling experience!  Divers who do this go with a medic team and backup at hand as the water is so cold you only get a short amount of time below before you have to come back up for warmth!

I’ll be back in Iceland in a few weeks but I *dont* think I’ll be doing any cold water swimming 🥶 #TheBohoDoesIceland

I never would have thought I would say that a destination is “sold out”… but welcome to 2023 and we are in full x games mode.

If you are searching for summer travel, there are many destinations that are nearly completely sold out for this summer, the top of that list being Japan & Italy! Greece is close behind and I can’t say I’m surprised.  While Europe is always busy in the summer, this year we have seen unprecedented levels of travel planning, and it’s only mid-February.
Our partners in Japan are saying there are no more tour guides available until after July, and our partners in Italy are letting us know that if you want to travel for 2 weeks, you’re probably going to need to up your budget from what you were expecting to pay!

SO I present to you, some destinations that are not entirely sold out!

ICELAND:  I love this place because it can truly be a year round destination as long as you don’t mind the cold!  Plus the perks of visiting during the winter mean northern lights!

PORTUGAL: For whatever reason, Portugal seems to be getting overlooked this year - and let me tell you, it should not be!  From incredible seafood and amazing architecture this culture rich country is worth the visit and has over 300+ days of sunshine each year!

SCOTLAND:  You know I can’t resist a trip to Scotland, and since it’s not already overbooked for the summer - neither should you!

MOROCCO:  If you’re looking for Spring travel, Morocco is a great fit if you want uniqueness and culture, without having to fly much further than Europe for it!

SPAIN: Honestly, you can never go wrong with a trip to Spain!
If you were looking for a sign to take a romantic getaway this year, here it is 🧡 happy Valentine’s Day! #TheBohoDoesScotland

I’ll paint the scene: Me @cpeshh - I think we should do a chill girl’s trip this year! Maybe Costa Rica or something? 
Oh look, tickets to Ecuador are $400 round trip? What about that?
🔔 It was not a chill trip 🔔 
BUT it was incredible!  We started off in Quito and went to Quilotoa and explored the Andes region of Ecuador.  After that we went down to Banos, which is an interesting place.  There are hot springs, and it feels like a rainforest, almost, but you’re definitely still up in the mountains. Banos when we visited was very misty and also gave me food poisoning.
After Banos we trekked into the Amazon Rainforest for a few days, me still with the food poisoning, convinced I am about to die.  This food poisoning, where if you have been following along for a while was the origin of Herman, my little stomach friend who I am convinced has ruined my stomach for life…I’ll have to explain that another time.  Regardless I felt horrible as I had to decline the entire fish the local Puyo family cooked me for dinner that night, though thankfully the Yuca Bread settled my stomach.

We hiked and explored the amazon, and stayed overnight in a tree house - real rustic, no lights, bring your own bedsheets sort of deal

I can’t remember how but we eventually made it to the Galapagos, after realising we had booked the locals ticket and needed to pay an additional $200 for the flight, then got swindled into checking our bags….another $200…if they tell you the plane is too small, I promise you it is NOT and then, we paid for the entrance to the Galapagos (expected) but another $100.

The Galapgos were incredible, and although not the “best” time of year to be there, I adored every second.  If you love nature and wildlife, this destination HAS to be at the top of your bucket list.

I tell you my bootleg story because, if you were wondering, I’ve made every travel mistake there is.  Seriously, there is probably very few mistakes in travel I haven’t made.

The way I travel now is vastly different from in 2019…but at heart, I am still a gritty traveller.  The biggest difference is now I want to put my head down in somewhere that has 5 stars attached 😜 #TheBohoDoesEcuador

🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 RANKED BELOW MY FAVORITE PLACES IN SCOTLAND 👇 

Ok, so actually it’s really hard to rank my favourite places to travel in Scotland, because I simply adore the whole country. Also, even though I never ever post about Italy, it still seems to be the only place you want, so right now I am going to try and convince you to go to Scotland for your next vacation!

1. Orkney Islands - This has been my favourite place to visit in Scotland so far!  Passage tombs, stone circles, highland coos and beautiful beaches, this place holds my heart!  Not to mention the famous Sara Brae!
2. Edinburgh - Truly riddled with amazing history, great food, and architecture that wows, no trip to Scotland is complete without a pitstop in Edinburgh.
3. Glencoe - Regarded by many as the gateway to the highlands and an incredible outdoor hub of the UK, Glencoe has much to offer for anyone not wanting to venture into the northern highlands.  Lochs abundant, bens and glens abound, Glencoe holds a host of activities for anyone!
4. Isle of Skye -  Not only a favourite of mine because some of my favourite whiskys are distilled there, but the scenery is unlike any other.  Old Man of Storr, the Quiraing, and Faerie Glen are some of the most unique landscapes I have ever seen.
5. Braemar - A favourite stomping ground of Queen Victoria, Braemar also holds one of my favourite hotels in the world, The Fife Arms.  You’ll know why when you see their whisky library.

I ALMOST FORGOT INVERNESS - lots of reasons here but most being, Outlander 🧡

PRACTICAL INFO FOR VISITING ICELAND 👇🏼👇🏼🇮🇸🇮🇸

🏨 If there was one thing I ever had to tell you I learned from this trip to Iceland it is: book early!!!!! There is still very limited accommodation in Iceland and the good stuff tends to fill up quickly.  If you need something specific or you are traveling in a group, this applies doubly for you!

📆 Best time of year to visit? It depends what you’re looking for!  Summer is going to be busy but there are endless hours of daylight for you to roam and explore (hello midnight sun!) and the landscape is green and the weather is a bit warmer. Winter allows you to see the northern lights and truly get the full “land of fire and ice” experience.

🧳 Packing in layers is a must: hot cars, busses and restaurants and freezing outside. Wear clothes you can easily get on and off. And make sure your outer layers are wind/water proof (full Iceland packing guide coming on the blog soon).

🚙 Self drive: it’s definitely possible but you will want the advice of a professional before you do this!  Working with a dedicated team in Iceland is a MUST in case things go wrong and to fully prep you for the adventure ahead!

Would you want to go to Iceland? Tag a friend who you want to go with in the comments! #TheBohoDoesIceland

Iceland is a place for the dreamers. The coastline is fickle. The skies are temperamental.  The landscape varies year by year.  The earth itself is moody.

I’ve travelled a bit in my 28 years of life & while there are many countries that captivate me, and I’ve found beauty everywhere I go- there are few that truly inspire the artist side of me and light that artist spark that lives in my bones.
Iceland is one of those places. It makes me want to write, paint, create, and above all, just play with the imagination inside of me.  It makes me want to buy a cottage in the middle of nowhere and scribble until my fingers fall off.

Last night I dreamed of the aurora. Earlier in the week I dreamed of cargo ships taking off into the atmosphere and creating tsunamis.
Something about this place feels different. It’s unexplainable, so I guess you need to come see it yourself. #TheBohoDoesIceland

Let’s talk about the Caribbean! 🌸

There are a lot of things that come into factor when deciding which island to visit!  We often hear about the Caribbean being discussed as one whole spot, but this is far from true!

When you use a travel advisor (hi, hello👋🏼) we discuss your must haves and will make a decision on where to send you based on that!

Some of these factors include: 

BEACH QUALITY
✨ long secluded beaches
✨intimate beach clubs
✨or forget the beach altogether - I’ll be at the pool!

WATER QUALITY
🌊 how important is perfectly clear water to you (this can vary with areas on the island not just by island!)

FOOD & DRINK
🍹all inclusive
🍹 local flavors
🍹 plenty of options

BUDGET & VALUE
💴 looking for a fun escape on a smaller budget? Your best options are going to be the Dominican Republic & Mexico. If you’re looking for all inclusive with white sand beaches and epic pools, your best choice will be St. Lucia or Antigua, but expect to have a higher spend here!

ACTIVITIES
🚙 are there things to do outside of the resort?
🚙 hot springs? Hiking? Horse riding? Day sailing? Yacht rental? Tequila or rum tastings?

So while we sometimes tend to lump “the Caribbean” into one big bundle- there are so many nuances!  When we schedule an intake call we’ll be sure to get all of this info from you and provide the best resort options for your desires! ☀️ #TheBohoDoesGuadeloupe

The Sky Lagoon just outside of Reykjavik is a new infinity hot spring overlooking the Atlantic Ocean - one breath and you feel as though you could topple into the endless frigid sea!

After changing into your swimming in the lush dressing rooms (equipped with showers and hair dryers) you enter a cave and stop into the steamy waters above Reykjavik.  Exploring the crevices leads you to hidden waterfalls, a massage area, and of course, the bar 😉

But to partake in the Viking Ritual is an absolute must! At the end of the Lagoon, is a hut, and this is where the magic happens - if you can drag yourself from the warmth.

1. Cold Plunge
2. Sauna
3. Cold Mist
4. Body Scrub
5. Steam Room
6. Shower
7. Hot Spring

And just like that…you’re as refreshed as Lagertha!  Soaking in the cold plunge was definitely the most challenging part of the ritual!! Would you try it?  #thebohodoesiceland

Feeling a lot of feels right now - I’m living a life I only could dream of for myself 5 years ago. Heading back to Spain today feels a little bit different than any other time I’ve left the US.
Who knew that being a digital nomad would come with a sort of peaceful existentialism?

Tomorrow there’s an apartment I know and love waiting for me to step into. My favorite person is arriving a few days later to join me in our little casita.  And while there’s no “job” on the other side, there are friends who have become family. There’s an entire life I didn’t realize I cultivated since I “accidentally” moved to palma in 2020.
There’s no return flight, but there is a monitor and keyboard that I’m sure are a little dusty from a few months of disuse and ready to audit some summer travel bookings.  Im cracking my fingers and so ready to service all this epic summer travel!
If you told 21 year old Sydney as she was moving to Italy for a summer (that turned into a year) this is where she would be in 7 years, she might have believed you, but wouldn’t begin to contemplate the path we took to get here.

And while I am so ready for tapas, wine, and a Spanish summer, (all which pair rather well with my general attitude on life) it gets a little bit harder to leave home every time.

Im so grateful for my people that keep me going every day.
Im so incredibly proud to have a thriving business I worked my booty off to craft and get to pour my heart into.
I am thankful for my clients, past and present- thank you thank you thank you for trusting me with some of your most important memories in life. 🧡

See you on the other side! #TheBohoDoesSpain

My poor little chapped nose at the end 😂 the first time I went to Iceland i had hair extensions… and I lost a lot of hair because of it. For those of you with long hair … you know how when you wear a scarf and your hair down it mats up in the back?  Okay well with fusion extensions it was 20x worse, and with the wind, exponentially so.  The extensions damaged my hair and ripped it out at the roots. I went to tape in extensions shortly after (so much better!) and my hair finally started to somewhat heal only after I chopped it all off and took out the extensions completely.

The thickness of my hair finally started coming back, but I didn’t see any progress on length until I chilled on the bleach and went back to my more natural color (what you see in this video!)

aaaaanyway, all that hair talk to say, braids are your BEST friend when visiting a windy place like Iceland, and I recommend pinning your bangs back or you’ll look like me 😂 #TheBohoDoesIceland

THE PROCESS: with every great work of art there is a process that comes along with it. Van Gogh did not simply throw paint upon a canvas and give us Starry Night - or maybe he did I don’t actually know that much about art, but what I can tell you is that with planning a trip there is a full step by step process to ensure you are 100% taken care of - no matter your depth of planning.

1. SUBMIT AN ENQUIRY ✨ the first step is the easiest.  Head to the link (it’s in my bio) and fill out the deets for your upcoming trip. Want tropical but don’t know where exactly? That’s OK, there’s a space for you to write that in.
2. SCHEDULE A CALL 💬 after the inquiry is filled out I’ll send you a link to schedule a call.  This is typically held on Google Meet so we can chat face to face and deep dive into your trip!
3. GET YOUR PROPOSAL 📑 after paying your planning fees within a week typically I will send you your proposal. Here you’ll have options for upgrades, downgrades and so much more. There will also be a Look video recording of my face walking you through the itinerary so you can understand it all perfectly.
4. BOOK THE TRIP ✈️ after you’ve made any tweaks or changes, we secure the booking!  This is usually held with a 20-30% deposit (it all just depends on the supplier requirements)
5. THE DETAILS 🍷 90 days out we’ll start capturing the little details and booking dining reservations for you.
6. GET ON THE FLIGHT 🧳 2-3 weeks prior to travel you will receive your documents and you are ready to go. Hit the skies and land in the custom curated holiday you could only dream of.

So, what’s stopping you?  Where is your next adventure?

The Olive tree in Palma is s’olivera de cort. She be old. Over 600 years old they say! But it’s not the oldest tree the island of Mallorca has on offer.

According to Mallorca news “Spain’s national prize of the “Best Monumental Olive Tree” in Spain was won by the Can Det olive tree. Not just because of age and size, but for the way in which it has been cared for by its owners, the local Deya Canals family of Soller.

The tree is estimated to be over 1,100 years old and was probably planted by the Muslims in the 9th century , its unique trunk measures more than 6.5 meters and continues to produce around 120 kg of olives per year.”

When you think of scotland you probably think of whisky, bagpipes, kilts and probably a certain Jamie Fraser.  But on a little island to the north, called Orkney, rests a myriad of neolithic ruins.
Most famous among these is the nearly perfectly preserved Skara Brae, but also passage tombs, burial chambers, and standing stones, such as the Ring of Brogan, and pictured here, the Stones of Stenness.
Similar to Stonehenge, we don’t really know why these stones are here, but they absolutely hold a power to them. If you’ve got a thing for ancient history (or Outlander) these stones are an essential addition to your bucket list!  #TheBohoDoesScotland #Scotland #Orkney #StonesofStenness

I don’t usually talk about Italy on here, and mostly for 2 reasons:
1. Italy sells itself - I could never make another post about Italy and it would probably still be at least 50% of my business
2. Even after living in Italy twice, visiting at least once a year for the last 7 years, and my love for the country - I don’t actually have that much Italy content (which sounds like to me it’s time to go on a FAM trip to fix that)

THAT BEING SAID….Here are some other destinations in Italy I absolutely adore that you should also add to your bucket list. They mightn’t be part of the Golden Trio, but they’re filled with incredible locals, have fabulous hotels, authentic experiences, and just as picturesque as anywhere else.

AND THIS IS THE MOMENT 👉🏼 I started my blog in 2016 because I received about one message a day asking me how I managed to move to Italy. So I took the assignment I had been given and created @thebohotraveller_llc

if you told 2016 me I would be living in the cutest apartment on an island in the med, I would have said “damn straight”. But probably would not believe all of the crazy incredible things I’ve done!

Those initial years growing the blog and this account were tough. Instagram was so different in those days, carousel posts had just launched. There were no video posts, no reels and I remember when stories launched everyone got mad that instagram was copying snapchat.

When I moved back to the US in 2017 I quickly got fed up.  I wanted to spend more time in Europe, less time working, but felt trapped.

In 2018 I took a course launched by an “influencer” that was $550 bucks and supposedly exclusive and would give away all her secrets. (I should have known better but I was young!) Over 500 students joined and the class was terrible. I won’t harp on about it but I got my money back.

I vowed never to take another course after that but then I bought a blogging bundle bc it had the presets of a photography company I loved and it included like 70 courses and so much more. That’s where I was introduced to @heleneinbetween 
I finally joined her instagram for success course in 2019, and everything changed. My account grew, I landed collabs, and I got a job with @explorateurtravel - from there the rest is history.
I don’t share anything on here I don’t truly believe in - and I’m not likely to ever launch an instagram course myself, bc Helene covers it all.  I can’t recommend this course enough for anyone who wants to digital nomad, market their business, or learn how to make money in this digital world.

Even if your concern isn’t growth, but learning how to make instagram work for your business- this course is for you.

After experiencing several flight cancellations and delays for clients this past weekend, I cannot stress enough how important it is to have “cancel for any reason” travel insurance. I know it can be tempting to skip out on travel insurance, but in times like these, it can truly be a lifesaver.

Travel is crazy this summer, and cancellations are unfortunately becoming much more common. Without insurance, you’re potentially risking losing a lot of money on non-refundable flights, hotels, and activities. But with “cancel for any reason” insurance, you’re able to protect yourself from unforeseen events and get reimbursed for your expenses if needed.

Don’t let the fear of a possible cancellation ruin your travel dreams. Take it from me – investing in “cancel for any reason” insurance is definitely worth the peace of mind. So next time you plan a trip, make sure you protect yourself and your wallet by purchasing travel insurance. Safe travels! ✈️🌍 #TravelInsurance #CancelForAnyReason #BohoTravel  #Wanderlust #TheBohoTraveller

Mykonos is all about the vibes 🧡
Nothing plays into the biggest part of the vibe like the hotel you stay at.
The last few days I have been hopping to several of the different hotels that i have not previously visited on the island to try and get a scope of even more offerings for my clients. There are some really important factors to consider when selecting your hotel in Mykonos

1. Location - taxis and transfers are not the most easily accessible in Mykonos, so if you want to go out a lot for food and drinks, you need to understand how far your hotel is from the places you are visiting or book somewhere within walking distance of a portion of them
2. Seclusion - do you want a hotel with a party vibe or do you want r&r?
3. Amenities- what’s your top priority? Private pool? Spa? Multiple restaurants? Sea view? Complimentary brekky? Beach club on site?

There really is a little bit for everyone in Mykonos 🧡

Last week I announced the launch of @thebohotraveller_llc as a full scale luxury travel agency. It was not something that happened overnight and I want to share a little bit about the background of The Boho Traveller, because obviously she is a labor of love very close to my heart 🧡
In 2016 i found myself moving to Florence Italy- a trip with, while with intentions of only staying 3 months, led me to staying an entire year.
When this accidental move happened, my degree from UF remained unfinished with a few semesters left.
Thanks to modern technology I completed 99% of my remaining coursework through online classes - and on.

During this class we had to start a blog, and at the time I received 1 message a week asking how I moved to Italy.
The blog I would start for this class was obvious- it was going to be a travel blog.

My first posts (as many blogs are) were pretty non sensical.  Then I started writing to help study abroad students in Florence, and I noticed how well those performed and were saved and shared.

I wrote about weekends in Paris, skiing in Switzerland, and of course all about life in Italy. At the time I worked at a student travel agency, running their blog and social media and getting a feel of what sort of future I could have in travel (I had no idea there was so much more to come).

When I moved back to the US the travel bug continued and I shared more about my travels, not just to Europe but to South America and Africa as well as the US.

The blog grew, and so did my instagram following.  I hit 10k, got a social media agent, started making money from brand collabs, and was proud of a self build blog bringing in almost 100k views a year. Small, but man, I did it all on my own!

In 2020 I started planning travel for clients under the Explorateur Travel brand. Working as an independent contractor under leadership there taught me the ropes of the travel industry and how to learn and grow.

After 2 full years, I knew I wanted more. At the beginning of this year I finally decided it was time - to have my own business and my own brand - taking Boho to the next level just felt right.

There’s more to the story - part 2 will come tomorrow!

As of tomorrow Spain has officially been “home” for three years!  And I really struggle to believe that 🫣
I also realized I never shared part 2 of @thebohotraveller_llc story so I’ll just answer one question that I always get asked “What’s a Boho?”

Boho is short for bohemian - socially unconventional in an artistic way. Which is sort of how I want to live my entire life and how I hope I curate my trips.

But Bohemia was also an area once ruled by the lands of the Bohemian Crown, now located and eventually dissolved into the Czech Republic. My ancestor, Otelia Smutney, was a duchess from this kingdom.  She severed ties with her royal family and ran away with her lover, a commoner named John Zaruba, from Romania, several years before the First World War.  Their son was born in Hungary and they later emigrated to the US.

Her story has always stuck with me and it became a part of the inspiration for the blog that has now become my travel agency 🧡

Many times you’ll know where you want to go, or what sort of trip you want, but you don’t know when to book that or when is even the best time to go! If I was planning a trip for next year (and I am for clients!) these are the trips I would be booking now & when I would recommend going!

CARIBBEAN & MEXICO
📆-> January & February
Seasonal depression is real & I know you’re not missing the sunshine yet- but come February I promise you will & have wish you booked the trip now when rates are lower!

ITALY 🇮🇹
📅 May, June, & September
As like last year, I am already seeing room categories for the earlier summer months in Italy selling out.  If you want to go to Italy next summer, book EARLY!  I also highly encourage you to travel to more off the beaten path destinations. The Amalfi coast is overwhelmed and there are plenty of other beautiful destinations in Italy that will cost you half the price for mediocre hotel.

SPAIN & PORTUGAL 🇪🇸 🇵🇹
📅-> June - September
Spain has stunning beaches, incredible small towns and amazing cuisine.  Portugal has fantastic wine and incredible culture. You really will not retreat this trip!

CROATIA 🇭🇷
📅 May - October
If you want Europe + beaches + a good price point - Croatia truly is a perfect fit!

UK & IRELAND 🇮🇪 🇬🇧
📆-> April - June
Springtime is already filling up in the UK with some of our preferred partners. Prices are higher than historically, so book early to avoid last minute rush pricing.

My favorite adventures of all time below 👇🏼 & how you can have them.

There’s a reason I keep going back to certain places - Morocco, Italy, Spain, Iceland, NYC, Scotland - because they are epic.

I’ve visited or lived in Italy every single year since 2015.

Morocco? Over 5 trips since 2018, 2 of those for multiple weeks.

Next year I am going on an immersive safari in South Africa with @personal.africa - and I’m so excited to finally explore a destination that has been on my bucketlist for ages!

You can go on these adventures too!  Planning a trip is hard work and no one wants their hard earned money to go somewhere mediocre.

When you trust a professional (who has been there! And knows and studies this for their living) you are making one the best investments for your memories.

Travel makes the world a little bit smaller, and our tolerance a little bit bigger. Learning from a new culture, trying a new food, getting lost in a new city, these are the stories we want to talk about.

Please please do not book your trips through Expedia or Air Bnb & come away with savage regrets bc your accommodation cancelled last minute while you were in flight and no one was there to back you up.

Take the time - write out your bucketlist, figure out what fuels you, then let a travel pro (hi, 👋🏼 hello 👋🏼 it’s me) take you on the adventure of a lifetime.

It is, in fact, the most wonderful time of the year 🎄 we are really enjoying the Christmas markets in Prague & Germany and can’t wait to share more on all the goodies and fun places 🧡 #TheBohoDoesGermany

This week at the Christmas markets in Germany was trying something out of our sugar plum dreams! 🧚🏻‍♀️ One of our favorite stops at the end of this trip was in Würzburg - from the history to the abundant market stalls, we loved all of it!

One important thing to know when you are visiting the Christmas markets is that the mugs you get with the glühwein you have ti pay a small deposit for - usually 2-5€ depending on the mug!  You can either keep these as a souvenir or return them to the stall to get your deposit back 🎄 we’ve returned with approximately 6 in our luggage after our @avalonwaterways cruise.
Adoring these German Christmas markers (and of course these travel tips). Not all markets are the same, so be sure to explore all of them that you come upon ❤️💚

Don’t sleep on Greece 🧡

For a destination that was never at the top of my bucket list, some forced proximity thanks to work totally changed my view of Greece.

For one - the Greeks know hospitality like no one else. Often in Europe I feel like the service or hospitality is not there and like I am a bother to staff for existing (IYKYK) , but this is almost never the case in Greece.

Im also obsessed with the boutique luxury hotel scene in Greece.  There are some amazing properties that truly have that “wow” factor and I want to send all of you to all of them!

The food and wine is also top notch, and I am still in search of a Greek salad to beat the one I had just by chance at a small shop while wandering the streets of Skyros during COVID. I’ve not yet had any luck but I try and replicate it myself at home as often as I can! (I also fail at this).

For me, going to Greece is like a ~very~ warm hug. It just feels right.
